# Backend Debug Logs in SRC

When running the backend in **debug mode**, write log files under the **SRC directory** so they are mounted into the Docker container and visible on the host.

The API service mounts `./src:/app/src`. Log paths must resolve inside that tree (e.g. under `backend/src/` on the host).

- **Do**: Resolve paths under `src` (e.g. `Path(__file__).resolve().parent` when the module is under `src`, or a subdir like `src/logs/`).
- **Don't**: Write debug logs to `/tmp`, `/app`, or anywhere outside `src` in Docker; those are not bound to the host.

```python
# Module under backend/src/ → log in same tree (mounted)
from pathlib import Path
DEBUG_LOG_PATH = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent / "debug.log"  # backend/src/debug.log
```
